    <p style="margin-top:var(--space-4)"><strong>BarOnly</strong> — recipe detail card progress bar (aria progressbar):</p>
    <div style="max-width:280px">
        <div class="meter__track rd-fulf-bar" role="progressbar" aria-valuenow="50" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
            <span class="meter__fill fulf-mid-bg" style="width:50%"></span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <pre class="code-sample"><code>@("<partial name=\"Shared/_Meter\" model='new MeterViewModel {\n    Percent  = pct,\n    Tone     = MeterViewModel.FulfTone(pct),\n    Layout   = MeterLayout.PctStack,\n    Label    = $\"{pct}%\",\n    SubLabel = $\"{inStock}/{total} in stock\"\n}' />")</code></pre>
</section>

<section class="catalog-section">
    <div class="catalog-section__header">
        <h2 class="catalog-section__heading">Stepper (<code>&lt;stepper&gt;</code> tag helper)</h2>
    </div>
    <p>
        The canonical −&nbsp;[value]&nbsp;+ primitive. Use the <code>&lt;stepper&gt;</code> tag helper — never
        hand-roll the markup. Three visual variants via CSS modifier; two structural modes (input vs display).
    </p>
    <p><strong>Default</strong> — 40 px icon buttons, rounded corners. Intake review qty, cook page qty, shopping add-form, inline-edit qty.</p>
    <div x-data="{ qty: 2 }" style="max-width:200px; margin-bottom: var(--space-4)">
        <stepper name="qty-demo"
                 x-model="qty"
                 decrease-click="qty = Math.max(0, qty - 1)"
                 increase-click="qty = qty + 1"
                 decrease-label="Decrease quantity"
                 increase-label="Increase quantity" />
    </div>
    <p><strong>compact</strong> — borderless square icon buttons inside a bordered container. Recipe-detail ingredients header.</p>
    <div x-data="{ servings: 4 }" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-4)">
        <stepper variant="compact"
                 group-label="Servings"
                 x-text="servings"
                 display-fallback="4"
                 decrease-click="servings = Math.max(1, servings - 1)"
                 increase-click="servings = Math.min(24, servings + 1)"
                 decrease-disabled="servings <= 1"
                 increase-disabled="servings >= 24"
                 decrease-label="Fewer servings"
                 increase-label="More servings" />
    </div>
    <p><strong>pill</strong> — 24 px circular text-glyph (−/+) buttons, inline flow. Recipe-meta strip servings.</p>
    <div x-data="{ servings: 4 }" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-4)">
        <stepper variant="pill"
                 group-label="Servings"
                 x-text="servings + (servings === 1 ? ' serving' : ' servings')"
                 display-fallback="4 servings"
                 decrease-click="servings = Math.max(1, servings - 1)"
                 increase-click="servings = servings + 1"
                 decrease-disabled="servings <= 1"
                 decrease-label="Fewer servings"
                 increase-label="More servings" />
    </div>
    <pre class="code-sample"><code>@("// Input mode (default variant)\n<stepper name=\"Edit.Quantity\" x-model=\"v\"\n         decrease-click=\"v = Math.max(0.001, (parseFloat(v)||0) - 1)\"\n         increase-click=\"v = (parseFloat(v)||0) + 1\"\n         decrease-label=\"Decrease quantity\" increase-label=\"Increase quantity\" />\n\n// Display mode, compact (recipe detail ingredients header)\n<stepper variant=\"compact\" group-label=\"Servings\" x-text=\"servings\" display-fallback=\"4\"\n         decrease-click=\"servings = Math.max(1, servings - 1); refreshFulfilment()\"\n         increase-click=\"servings = Math.min(24, servings + 1); refreshFulfilment()\"\n         decrease-disabled=\"servings <= 1\" increase-disabled=\"servings >= 24\"\n         decrease-label=\"Fewer servings\" increase-label=\"More servings\" />")</code></pre>
</section>

@*
    ── Recipe editor components (P2-1d) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    These components are the building blocks of the recipe author/edit form (J6/J7). They are
    added to the library here first, then consumed by Pages/Recipes/Edit.cshtml.
*@

<section class="catalog-section">
    <div class="catalog-section__header">
        <h2 class="catalog-section__heading">Ingredient row editor (<code>.ingredient-row</code>)</h2>
    </div>
    <p>
        <code>.ingredient-row</code> is one editable ingredient line in the recipe editor (J6/J7).
        Each row has: a drag handle, a product search field (htmx-driven <code>searchableSelect</code>),
        a quantity + unit pair (hidden for untracked staples, C12), an optional group heading, and a delete
        button. Rows are rendered by an Alpine <code>x-for</code> template loop that keeps draft state
        per row (ADR-005). The <code>.ingredient-row--needs-conversion</code> modifier applies a warning
        left-border when a <code>NeedsConversion</code> result is returned (C10).
        An inline staple-create escape hatch (C12) replaces the product-search field with a plain text
        input when the user clicks <em>Create as staple</em>.
    </p>
    <p>
        Drag-reorder is native HTML5 drag: <code>draggable="true"</code> + Alpine event handlers
        <code>dragStart(idx)</code> / <code>dragOver(idx)</code> / <code>drop()</code> that splice
        the <code>rows[]</code> array and call <code>reassignOrdinals()</code> so hidden ordinal inputs
        stay contiguous. This mirrors the <code>_SortableList</code> pattern (htmx POST on drop) but
        is entirely Alpine-owned because the ingredient list is not persisted until submit.
    </p>
    <div class="card" style="max-width: 48rem">
        <div class="card__body" style="padding: 0" x-data="{ rows: [{ id: 1, product: 'Whole milk', qty: '2', unit: 'cup', group: '' }], dragIdx: null }">
            <div id="ingredient-rows-demo">
                <template x-for="(row, idx) in rows" :key="row.id">
                    <div class="ingredient-row" draggable="true"
                         @@dragstart.self="dragIdx = idx"
                         @@dragover.prevent="if (dragIdx !== null && dragIdx !== idx) { const m = rows.splice(dragIdx, 1)[0]; rows.splice(idx, 0, m); dragIdx = idx; }"
                         @@drop="dragIdx = null">
                        <div class="ingredient-row__body">
                            <div class="ingredient-row__drag" aria-hidden="true" style="cursor:grab;color:var(--color-text-muted);padding:var(--space-2);display:flex;align-items:center">
                                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><line x1="3" y1="8" x2="21" y2="8"/><line x1="3" y1="16" x2="21" y2="16"/></svg>
                            </div>
                            <input type="text" class="field__input" placeholder="Search products…" :value="row.product" style="flex:2;min-width:0" />
                            <input type="number" class="field__input" placeholder="Qty" :value="row.qty" style="width:5rem;text-align:center;flex-shrink:0" />
                            <select class="field__input" style="min-width:5rem;flex-shrink:0">
                                <option>cup</option><option>g</option><option>ea</option>
                            </select>
                            <input type="text" class="field__input" placeholder="Group" :value="row.group" style="flex:1;min-width:0;font-size:var(--font-size-sm)" />
                            <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm" @@click="rows.splice(idx, 1)" style="flex-shrink:0;color:var(--color-danger)">
                                <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#i-minus" /></svg>
                            </button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </template>
            </div>
            <div style="padding: var(--space-4)">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm" @@click="rows.push({ id: Date.now(), product: '', qty: '', unit: '', group: '' })">
                    <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#i-plus" /></svg>
                    Add ingredient
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <pre class="code-sample"><code>@("// Alpine x-data on the outer container:\n// rows: [{ ordinal, productId, productName, qty, unitId, groupHeading, isUntracked, ... }]\n// addRow(), removeRow(idx), dragStart(idx), dragOver(idx), drop(), reassignOrdinals()\n\n// Each row:\n<div class=\"ingredient-row\" draggable=\"true\" :class=\"{'ingredient-row--needs-conversion': row.needsConversion}\"\n     @dragstart.self=\"dragStart(idx)\" @dragover.prevent=\"dragOver(idx)\" @drop=\"drop()\">\n  <div class=\"ingredient-row__body\">\n    <div class=\"ingredient-row__drag\"><!-- drag handle icon --></div>\n    <!-- product search, qty, unit, group heading, delete -->\n  </div>\n  <!-- inline conversion form shown when row.needsConversion -->\n</div>")</code></pre>
</section>

<section class="catalog-section">
    <div class="catalog-section__header">
        <h2 class="catalog-section__heading">Tag picker — type-to-filter chips (closed vocabulary)</h2>
    </div>
    <p>
        The recipe tag editor is a chip-based multi-select over a <strong>read-only, household-defined vocabulary</strong>.
        A text input filters the active defined tags into a dropdown; selecting one adds it as a chip.
        Typing a brand-new name does <em>not</em> create anything — no Enter/comma mint.
        Backspace with an empty input removes the last chip; clicking elsewhere closes the dropdown.
    </p>
    <p>
        Alpine state: <code>tags</code> is an array of <code>&#123;id, name&#125;</code> objects; <code>tagOptions</code>
        is the full active-tag list from the server (serialised once via <code>JsonSerializer.Serialize</code>
        without <code>Html.Raw</code>). Hidden inputs post <code>Input.TagIds</code> (one per chip).
        The dropdown offers only active tags not already selected — <code>filteredTagOptions()</code> excludes
        both already-selected and non-matching options. Clicking an option calls <code>addTagFromOption(opt)</code>
        via <code>@@mousedown.prevent</code> so the input blur does not fire before the click registers.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Empty-household state:</strong> when <code>Model.TagOptions</code> is empty (the household
        has no active tags), the picker body shows a guidance message linking to <code>/Settings/Tags</code>
        — rendered server-side (no Alpine branch needed) because <code>TagOptions</code> is known at render time.
    </p>
    @{
        var demoTagOpts = System.Text.Json.JsonSerializer.Serialize(new[]
        {
            new { id = "aaa", name = "Breakfast" },
            new { id = "bbb", name = "Quick" },
            new { id = "ccc", name = "Vegetarian" },
            new { id = "ddd", name = "Weeknight" },
        });
    }
    <div style="max-width: 36rem"
         x-data="{
             tags: [{ id: 'bbb', name: 'Quick' }],
             tagQuery: '',
             tagDropOpen: false,
             tagOptions: @demoTagOpts,
             filteredTagOptions() {
                 const q = this.tagQuery.trim().toLowerCase();
                 return this.tagOptions.filter(o =>
                     !this.tags.some(t => t.id === o.id) &&
                     (!q || o.name.toLowerCase().includes(q)));
             },
             addTagFromOption(opt) {
                 if (!this.tags.some(t => t.id === opt.id))
                     this.tags.push({ id: opt.id, name: opt.name });
                 this.tagQuery = '';
                 this.tagDropOpen = false;
                 this.$nextTick(() => this.$refs.tagInputDemo.focus());
             },
             removeTag(i) { this.tags.splice(i, 1); },
         }">
        <template x-for="(tag, ti) in tags" :key="tag.id">
            <input type="hidden" name="Input.TagIds" :value="tag.id" />
        </template>
        <div style="position:relative">
            <div class="recipe-tag-editor"
                 style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:var(--space-2);align-items:center;border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:var(--radius-md);padding:var(--space-2) var(--space-3);min-height:2.5rem;cursor:text"
                 @@click="$refs.tagInputDemo.focus()">
                <template x-for="(tag, ti) in tags" :key="tag.id">
                    <span class="badge badge--neutral" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:var(--space-1)">
                        <span x-text="tag.name"></span>
                        <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm" style="padding:0 2px;line-height:1;font-size:inherit" aria-label="Remove tag" @@click.stop="removeTag(ti)">×</button>
                    </span>
                </template>
                <input type="text" x-ref="tagInputDemo" x-model="tagQuery"
                       placeholder="Filter tags…"
                       class="field__input"
                       style="border:none;outline:none;box-shadow:none;padding:0;min-width:8rem;flex:1"
                       @@focus="tagDropOpen = true"
                       @@input="tagDropOpen = true"
                       @@keydown.escape="tagDropOpen = false; tagQuery = ''"
                       @@keydown.backspace="if (!tagQuery && tags.length) removeTag(tags.length - 1)"
                       autocomplete="off" />
            </div>
            <div x-show="tagDropOpen && filteredTagOptions().length > 0"
                 x-cloak
                 @@click.outside="tagDropOpen = false"
                 style="position:absolute;z-index:50;left:0;right:0;margin-top:2px;background:var(--color-surface);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:var(--radius-md);max-height:12rem;overflow-y:auto;box-shadow:var(--shadow-md)">
                <template x-for="opt in filteredTagOptions()" :key="opt.id">
                    <button type="button"
                            class="tag-picker-option"
                            style="display:block;width:100%;text-align:left;padding:var(--space-2) var(--space-3);background:none;border:none;cursor:pointer;font:inherit;color:var(--color-text)"
                            @@mousedown.prevent="addTagFromOption(opt)"
                            x-text="opt.name"></button>
                </template>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size:var(--font-size-sm);color:var(--color-text-muted);margin:var(--space-2) 0 0">
            Try typing to filter. Selected: <code x-text="JSON.stringify(tags)"></code>
        </p>
    </div>
    <style>
        .recipe-tag-editor:focus-within { border-color: var(--color-accent); }
        .tag-picker-option:hover { background: var(--color-surface-2) !important; }
    </style>
    <pre class="code-sample"><code>@("// Page model: TagOptions populated via tags.ListAllAsync(activeOnly: true)\n// Server-side JSON (without Html.Raw):\n// var tagsInitJson = JsonSerializer.Serialize(Input.TagIds.Zip(Input.TagNames, (id, name) => new { id, name }).ToList());\n// var tagOptionsJson = JsonSerializer.Serialize(TagOptions.Select(o => new { id = o.Value, name = o.Text }).ToList());\n\n// Alpine x-data (substitute serialised JSON for the two variables):\n// tags: <tagsInitJson>,           // [{id, name}, ...] — pre-selected chips (incl. archived)\n// tagOptions: <tagOptionsJson>,    // [{id, name}, ...] — active defined tags only\n// filteredTagOptions() — excludes already-selected and non-matching\n// addTagFromOption(opt) — pushes chip, clears query, closes dropdown\n// removeTag(i) — splices from tags[]\n\n// Hidden inputs post the TagId array (one per chip):\n<template x-for=\"(tag, ti) in tags\" :key=\"tag.id\">\n  <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"Input.TagIds\" :value=\"tag.id\" />\n</template>\n\n// Chip + filter input container:\n<div class=\"recipe-tag-editor\" @click=\"$refs.tagInput.focus()\">\n  <template x-for=\"(tag, ti) in tags\" :key=\"tag.id\">\n    <span class=\"badge badge--neutral\">\n      <span x-text=\"tag.name\"></span>\n      <button type=\"button\" @click.stop=\"removeTag(ti)\">x</button>\n    </span>\n  </template>\n  <input type=\"text\" x-ref=\"tagInput\" x-model=\"tagQuery\" placeholder=\"Filter tags…\"\n         @focus=\"tagDropOpen = true\" @input=\"tagDropOpen = true\"\n         @keydown.escape=\"tagDropOpen = false; tagQuery = ''\"\n         @keydown.backspace=\"if (!tagQuery && tags.length) removeTag(tags.length - 1)\"\n         autocomplete=\"off\" />\n</div>\n\n// Dropdown:\n<div x-show=\"tagDropOpen && filteredTagOptions().length > 0\" x-cloak @click.outside=\"tagDropOpen = false\"\n     style=\"position:absolute;...\">\n  <template x-for=\"opt in filteredTagOptions()\" :key=\"opt.id\">\n    <button type=\"button\" class=\"tag-picker-option\" @mousedown.prevent=\"addTagFromOption(opt)\" x-text=\"opt.name\"></button>\n  </template>\n</div>\n\n// Empty-household server-side guidance (when Model.TagOptions is empty):\n<p>No tags defined yet. <a href=\"/Settings/Tags\">Manage tags in Settings</a>.</p>")</code></pre>
</section>

<section class="catalog-section">
    <div class="catalog-section__header">
        <h2 class="catalog-section__heading">Servings scale offer (J7 step 3)</h2>
    </div>
    <p>
        On the recipe edit form, when the user changes the <em>Default servings</em> value on a recipe
        that already has ingredients, a <code>.seg-ctrl</code> toggle appears asking whether to
        <strong>Proportional</strong>ly scale the ingredient quantities or <strong>Keep</strong> them
        as-is. Alpine controls visibility via <code>showScaleOffer()</code> which returns true when
        <code>servings !== origServings &amp;&amp; hasIngredients</code>. The selected mode posts via a
        hidden input (<code>Input.ScaleMode</code>) which <code>AuthorRecipe</code> applies during the
        <code>Recipe.ChangeDefaultServings</code> call.
    </p>
    <div style="max-width: 36rem" x-data="{ servings: 4, origServings: 4, scaleMode: 'Keep', hasIngredients: true, showOffer() { return this.hasIngredients && this.servings !== this.origServings; } }">
        <div class="form-stack" style="gap:var(--space-3)">
            <div class="form-grid">
                <field stacked asp-for="FieldRowDemo.Quantity">
                    <input type="number" class="field__input" x-model.number="servings" min="1" step="1" />
                </field>
            </div>
            <div class="card" x-show="showOffer()" x-cloak>
                <div class="card__head">
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="card__head-title">Scale ingredients?</h3>
                        <p class="card__head-sub">You changed the default servings. How should ingredient quantities be adjusted?</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card__body">
                    <div class="seg-ctrl" role="group" aria-label="Scale mode">
                        <label class="seg-ctrl__item">
                            <input type="radio" name="demo-scale" value="Proportional" x-model="scaleMode" />
                            <span>Proportional — scale quantities</span>
                        </label>
                        <label class="seg-ctrl__item">
                            <input type="radio" name="demo-scale" value="Keep" x-model="scaleMode" />
                            <span>Keep — preserve quantities</span>
                        </label>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size:var(--font-size-sm);color:var(--color-text-muted);margin:var(--space-2) 0 0">
            Change the servings from 4 to something else to see the offer appear.
        </p>
    </div>
    <pre class="code-sample"><code>@("// Alpine: showScaleOffer() { return !isCreate && hasIngredients && parseInt(servings) !== origServings; }\n// Hidden input posts selected mode:\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"Input.ScaleMode\" :value=\"scaleMode\" />\n\n<div class=\"card\" x-show=\"showScaleOffer()\" x-cloak>\n  <div class=\"card__body\">\n    <div class=\"seg-ctrl\" role=\"group\" aria-label=\"Scale mode\">\n      <label class=\"seg-ctrl__item\">\n        <input type=\"radio\" name=\"_scaleMode\" value=\"Proportional\" x-model=\"scaleMode\" />\n        <span>Proportional — scale quantities</span>\n      </label>\n      <label class=\"seg-ctrl__item\">\n        <input type=\"radio\" name=\"_scaleMode\" value=\"Keep\" x-model=\"scaleMode\" />\n        <span>Keep — preserve quantities</span>\n      </label>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>")</code></pre>
</section>

@*
    ── P4-6: Product search / create sheet ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Shared _ProductSearchCreateSheet partial — extracted from Recipes/Edit and reused by Take Stock
    inline-add (P4-7, plantry-hcj3.8). Added here first per the component-library-first convention.
*@

<section class="catalog-section">
    <div class="catalog-section__header">
        <h2 class="catalog-section__heading">Product search / create sheet (<code>Shared/_ProductSearchCreateSheet</code>)</h2>
    </div>
    <p>
        <code>Shared/_ProductSearchCreateSheet</code> is the shared bottom-drawer for picking or
        creating a catalog product. It provides two modes: a type-to-search product picker (htmx-driven
        <code>searchableSelect</code>) and an inline staple-create escape hatch (C12) that lets the user
        type a name and default unit when no match exists.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Fuzzy search + ranking (plantry-hl4a):</strong> the search endpoints backing this control
        (<code>OnGetSearchProducts</code> on Recipes/Edit and Pantry/TakeStock/Walk) both run the shared
        <code>ProductNameMatcher</code> ranker — tolerant of plurals, typos, and word-order differences.
        Results appear as a ranked inline list: each <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> carries a
        <code>&lt;span class="rk"&gt;</code> label (<code>best</code> for the top hit, <code>N%</code>
        for the rest), using the same vocabulary as Intake's <code>.match-suggest</code> family.
        The <code>+ Create …</code> button is <strong>demoted</strong> (ghost style) whenever the listbox
        has results (score ≥ 0.70 cleared); it is full-strength only when nothing matches.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Relationship to <code>.match-suggest</code> (Intake):</strong> both surfaces belong to
        the same "match suggestion" family — ranked results with <code>best</code>/<code>N%</code> labels
        via <code>.rk</code> — but they use deliberately different mechanisms. Intake's
        <code>AlternativesStrip</code> shows AI-precomputed candidates unprompted (hence a "Did you mean"
        header); this control reacts as-you-type from a deterministic fuzzy ranker (no header needed). Do
        NOT unify the implementations. Cross-reference: see the <em>Match suggest ("Did you mean")</em>
        section on this page for the Intake family member.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Alpine contract:</strong> the host page's <code>x-data</code> must expose
        <code>sheetOpen</code>, <code>editingIdx</code> (null = adding, number = editing),
        <code>draft</code> (working copy of the row), <code>closeSheet()</code>, <code>saveSheet()</code>,
        and <code>selectProduct(row, detail)</code>.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Event contract:</strong>
    </p>
    <ul style="font-size:var(--font-size-sm)">
        <li><code>sheet-product-set</code> (window) — dispatched inbound by the host when opening the sheet to
            pre-populate the search box (<code>detail: label string</code>).</li>
        <li><code>pick-product</code> — dispatched outbound from each search result <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> on click.
            <code>detail: &#123; value: ProductId, name, track: "true"|"false" &#125;</code>.
            The host catches it on the sheet element via <code>@@pick-product="selectProduct(draft, $event.detail)"</code>.</li>
        <li><code>product-search-create</code> — dispatched outbound by the search component's create button
            (plantry-gzro). <code>detail: &#123; query: string &#125;</code>. The sheet catches it on the sheet
            element and sets <code>sheetView = 'create'</code>, seeding <code>draft.newStapleName</code> from the query.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        <strong>Parameters (<code>ProductSearchCreateSheetViewModel</code>):</strong>
    </p>
    <ul style="font-size:var(--font-size-sm)">
        <li><code>SearchUrl</code> — htmx endpoint (<code>hx-get</code>) returning <code>&lt;li role="option"&gt;</code> markup with <code>.rk</code> ranking labels.</li>
        <li><code>UnitOptions</code> — units for the staple-create unit select and (when <code>TrackStock</code> is true) the ingredient unit select.</li>
        <li><code>TrackStock</code> — when true (Recipes), qty + unit fields appear for tracked products.
            When false (Take Stock inline-add) those fields are hidden; count lives in the extra-fields slot.</li>
        <li><code>ExtraFieldsPartial</code> — optional partial name rendered between the product picker and action bar (e.g. Take Stock count + location fields for P4-7).</li>
        <li><code>Noun</code> — noun used in the sheet header and aria-label: "Add {Noun}" / "Edit {Noun}". Default: <code>"ingredient"</code> (Recipes). Pass <code>"item"</code> for Take Stock.</li>
        <li><code>ShowGroupHeading</code> — when false, hides the "Group (optional)" field (a Recipes-only concept). Default: <code>true</code>. Take Stock passes <code>false</code>.</li>
        <li><code>CreateLabel</code> — trailing phrase in the search component's create button, e.g. <code>+ Create "chicken" {CreateLabel}</code>. Default: <code>"as a new staple"</code>. Take Stock passes <code>"as a new product"</code> (the action is actually tracked there).</li>
        <li><code>StapleNamePlaceholder</code> — placeholder for the name input in create mode. Default: <code>"Staple name (e.g. Salt)"</code>. Pass neutral wording for non-Recipes contexts.</li>
    </ul>

    @*
        Live demo wrapped in a minimal Alpine host satisfying the sheet's x-data contract.
        Uses /Dev?handler=FilterGroceries (same endpoint as the searchable-select demo) so the
        picker works without a full recipe-page context.
    *@
    <div style="max-width: 36rem"
         x-data="{
             sheetOpen: false,
             editingIdx: null,
             draft: {},
             blankDraft() {
                 return { productId: '', productName: '', isUntracked: false,
                          newStapleName: null, newStapleUnit: '', newStapleCategoryId: '',
                          qty: '', unitId: '', groupHeading: '' };
             },
             openSheet() {
                 this.editingIdx = null;
                 this.draft = this.blankDraft();
                 this.sheetOpen = true;
                 this.$nextTick(() => window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('sheet-product-set', { detail: '' })));
             },
             closeSheet() { this.sheetOpen = false; },
             saveSheet() { this.sheetOpen = false; },
             selectProduct(row, detail) {
                 row.productId = detail.value;
                 row.productName = detail.name;
                 row.isUntracked = detail.track === 'false';
             },
         }">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--secondary" @@click="openSheet()">Open sheet demo</button>
        <p x-show="!sheetOpen" style="font-size:var(--font-size-sm);color:var(--color-text-muted);margin:var(--space-2) 0 0">
            Click to open the shared sheet. Fuzzy search: try "tomatos", "oat milks", "ched", or a query
            that returns no matches to see the create button shift to full-strength.
        </p>

        <partial name="Shared/_ProductSearchCreateSheet"
                 model='new Plantry.Web.Pages.Shared.ProductSearchCreateSheetViewModel
                 {
                     SearchUrl   = "/Dev?handler=FilterGroceries",
                     UnitOptions = Model.UnitOptions,
                     TrackStock  = true,
                 }' />
    </div>

    <pre class="code-sample"><code>@(@"// View-model (all params — defaults preserve Recipes behaviour)
new ProductSearchCreateSheetViewModel
{
    SearchUrl             = Url.Page(""./MyPage"", ""SearchProducts"")!,
    UnitOptions           = Model.UnitOptions,              // IReadOnlyList<SelectListItem>
    TrackStock            = true,                           // false = hide qty/unit (Take Stock)
    ExtraFieldsPartial    = null,                           // or ""TakeStock/_CountLocationFields""
    Noun                  = ""ingredient"",                  // 'Add {Noun}' / 'Edit {Noun}' in title
    ShowGroupHeading      = true,                           // false hides the Recipes-only Group field
    CreateLabel           = ""as a new staple"",              // trailing phrase: '+ Create ""x"" {CreateLabel}'
    StapleNamePlaceholder = ""Staple name (e.g. Salt)"",     // placeholder in create-mode name input
}

// Search endpoints must return <li role=""option""> markup with .rk ranking labels:
//   <li role=""option"" data-value=""{id}"" data-name=""{html-encoded name}""
//       data-track=""true|false"" data-default-unit=""{unitId}""
//       @click=""query = $el.dataset.name; open = false; $dispatch('pick-product', ...)"">
//     {name}<span class=""rk"">best</span>   <!-- or: 87% -->
//   </li>
// Use ProductNameMatcher.RankLabel(score, isTopHit) to generate the label.

// Host x-data must expose:
//   sheetOpen, editingIdx, draft, closeSheet(), saveSheet(),
//   selectProduct(row, detail)   ← catches the pick-product event

// Usage:
<partial name=""Shared/_ProductSearchCreateSheet"" model=""Model.SheetVm"" />

// Or inline (page with Url helper):
<partial name=""Shared/_ProductSearchCreateSheet""
         model='new ProductSearchCreateSheetViewModel
         {
             SearchUrl = Url.Page(""./Edit"", ""SearchProducts"")!,
             UnitOptions = Model.UnitOptions,
             TrackStock = true,
         }' />")</code></pre>
</section>

<section class="catalog-section">
    <div class="catalog-section__header">
        <h2 class="catalog-section__heading">Recipes browse — fulfillment pill (gallery)</h2>
    </div>
    <p>
        <code>.fulf-pill</code> overlays the gallery card scrim. Translucent white background with
        blur, colored status dot (<code>.fulf-pill__dot</code>, background from <code>.fulf-hi-bg</code>
        / <code>.fulf-mid-bg</code> / <code>.fulf-lo-bg</code>) and percentage text.
    </p>
